geek","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/y18ubq2knU2KqHx1oSyWN2dK/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":null},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"omise","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":5248757,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"When you login two times, you get two different sessions. That is expected behaviour to allow you to stay logged in on different devices. \n\nI agree that there is room for improvement. But probably this will go under good advice. There is no real direct exploit here. Will discuss with team. I think the nice behaviour is\n\n- Show what sessions are alive. And allow revoke other sessions by user when doing a password change if he want. If he don't want. That is ok also. As long as can see all sessions.\n","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2019-07-04T01:35:55.119Z","updated_at":"2019-07-04T01:35:55.119Z","actor":{"username":"hardymansen","cleared":false,"url":"/hardymansen","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/268/510/a5be384b5218b68c9ed291e2649c3a659f9baeb5_original.jpg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":null},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"omise","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":5248758,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BugTriaged","message":"Hi, \n\nWe have verified your report.\nThank you again. We will get back to you when we have a resolution. \n\nOmise Security","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2019-07-04T01:36:30.473Z","updated_at":"2019-07-04T01:37:00.905Z","actor":{"username":"hardymansen","cleared":false,"url":"/hardymansen","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-co